body:
@mmstick That is understandable, but that's no different for me either. It has been brought up multiple times and there is the option to subscribe to releases to get notifications about new versions.

I'm not blaming you for this, if you're too busy with other stuff that's perfectly fine. But I just cannot in good faith recommend a PPA that is outdated for so long since it directly increases the amount of emails I get every day. :smile: 

I'll be very happy to add it again when I have more confidence in its availability, but after having just removed it because of these concerns I want to give it at least a version or two to ensure that these problems are not the status quo. I would appreciate if you keep this PPA available since it has been of significant value to our Ubuntu/Mint/... users based on the feedback I've gotten.
